<subSubSection id="1448F3B44CC0F9D7C081BFF406A99F62" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B88BA0DB8F51177B79B17723C18549D3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5FF292A38B4D1D968A01ECB396650634" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Amongst Brazilian species of 
<taxonomicName id="742A888BE961F6E281072B05EAE388F0" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Ipomoea" order="Solanales" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CE837C0B1E5A8B35C7E36C6363BFE0BA" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Ipomoea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A720AF7A0FEB48F124716460FBB09D20" genus="I." lsidName="I. scopulina" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="scopulina">
<emphasis id="19BE2BB49D1B0A607CCF4C3F5AF6A9A8" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">I. scopulina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles only 
<taxonomicName id="CDD8CC43821637F9825AFEC6B1061BAC" genus="I." lsidName="I. longistaminea" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="longistaminea">
<emphasis id="98D9EAF24CC04BEEB712815A7209FEF1" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">I. longistaminea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="00A029022637004B5B39A19A1F9361B9" originalValue="O’Donell">O'Donell</normalizedToken>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6EAC5EE955CF5AD77EC280F1FDB28725" genus="I." lsidName="I. ana-mariae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" rank="species" species="ana-mariae">
<emphasis id="04E98681E30D67CEB7BBCEA66A5400E2" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">I. ana-mariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L.V.Vasconcelos &amp; Sim.-Bianch in having a cylindrical suburceolate corolla but is distinguished from both of these by the broadly lanceolate subacute (not oblong-elliptic, coriaceous, somewhat concave) sepals.
</paragraph>
